  "text": "## Grafana Dashboard JSON Model Version Migration Implementation\n\nGrafana implements a comprehensive dashboard JSON schema versioning and migration system across both frontend (TypeScript) and backend (Go) layers. The current schema version is **42**, which is marked as final for the v1 dashboard API.\n\n### Frontend TypeScript Migration Layer\n\nThe frontend migration is implemented in `public/app/features/dashboard/state/DashboardMigrator.ts`, which defines `DASHBOARD_SCHEMA_VERSION = 42` and the `DashboardMigrator` class. This class implements the `updateSchema()` method that handles schema version migrations (v0-v42) directly in the browser. The related models are in:\n\n- `DashboardModel.ts` - Main dashboard data model with constructor defaults\n- `PanelModel.ts` - Panel model with panel-specific defaults and migrations\n- `TimeModel.ts` - Time range model\n\n### Backend Go Migration System\n\nThe backend migration system is located in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/` and handles dashboard schema version migrations at runtime:\n\n#### Core Migration Orchestrator\n- `migrate.go` - Main migration entry point with `Migrate()` function and `Initialize()` for dependency setup. Coordinates the migration pipeline including frontend defaults, schema version migrations, and cleanup.\n- `frontend_defaults.go` - Applies DashboardModel and PanelModel constructor defaults to match frontend behavior\n- `metrics.go` - Provides observability through metrics tracking\n\n#### Schema Version Migrations\n- `schemaversion/migrations.go` - Core registry that defines `GetMigrations()` which maps schema versions (v2-v42) to their respective migration functions. Defines `SchemaVersionMigrationFunc` type and constants `LATEST_VERSION = 42` and `MIN_VERSION = 0`.\n- `schemaversion/errors.go` - Error types including `MigrationError` and `MinimumVersionError`\n- `schemaversion/v2.go` through `schemaversion/v42.go` - Individual migration functions (V2-V42) for each schema version. For example:\n  - `V2` - Migrates legacy `services.filter` structure to modern `time` and `templating`\n  - `V33` - Migrates datasource references from string names to structured UIDs using `DataSourceIndexProvider`\n  - `V42` - Ensures fields hidden from visualization are also hidden from tooltips\n\n#### Migration Utilities\n- `schemaversion/migration_utils.go` - Helper functions like `GetStringValue()`, `GetBoolValue()`, `GetIntValue()`, `GetFloatValue()` for safe type conversions\n- `schemaversion/cache.go` - TTL-based caching mechanism with `cachedProvider` type for indexing datasources and library elements\n- `schemaversion/datasource_utils.go` - `DatasourceIndex` for O(1) datasource lookups, `WrapIndexProviderWithCache()` for caching provider results\n\n### Conversion Layer\n\nThe conversion layer in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/conversion/` handles transformations between different API versions:\n\n- `conversion.go` - Defines `DashboardConversion` interface and `RegisterConversions()` function that registers converters between API versions\n- `v0.go`, `v1.go`, `v2.go` - Version-specific conversion implementations\n- `v0alpha1_to_v1beta1.go` - Converts v0alpha1 dashboards to v1beta1\n- `v1beta1_to_v2alpha1.go` - Converts v1beta1 dashboards to v2alpha1\n- `v2alpha1_to_v1beta1.go` - Reverse conversion from v2alpha1 to v1beta1\n- `v2alpha1_to_v2beta1.go` - Converts v2alpha1 to v2beta1\n- `v2beta1_to_v2alpha1.go` - Reverse conversion from v2beta1 to v2alpha1\n- `conversion_data_loss_detection.go` - Detects and tracks data loss during conversions\n- `errors.go` and `metrics.go` - Error handling and observability for conversions\n\n### Legacy SQL Migration\n\nThe legacy SQL storage migration is implemented in `pkg/registry/apis/dashboard/legacy/`:\n\n- `sql_dashboards.go` - Implements `MigrateDashboards()` method that reads dashboards from legacy SQL storage and streams them to unified storage\n- `types.go` - Defines `Migrator` interface with methods `MigrateDashboards()`, `MigrateFolders()`, `MigrateLibraryPanels()`\n- `storage.go`, `client.go`, `context.go`, `queries.go`, `token.go` - Supporting infrastructure for legacy storage access\n\n### Migration Coordination\n\n- `pkg/registry/apis/dashboard/migrator/migrator.go` - Implements `FoldersDashboardsMigrator` interface via `foldersDashboardsMigrator` struct and `ProvideFoldersDashboardsMigrator()` function\n- `pkg/registry/apis/dashboard/migration_registrar.go` - Registers the dashboard migration with the unified migration registry\n\n### Schema Definition and Validation\n\n- `pkg/kinds/dashboard/addenda.go` - Defines `HandoffSchemaVersion = 36` as the minimum schema version for Thema-based validation\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/apis/dashboard/v0alpha1/validation.go` and `v1beta1/validation.go` - Schema validation using `ValidateDashboardSpec()`\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/apis/dashboard/v0alpha1/conversion.go`, `v1beta1/conversion.go`, `v2alpha1/conversion.go`, `v2beta1/conversion.go` - Generated and manual conversion implementations\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Dual-Path Migration**: Dashboards can be migrated either on the frontend (older versions) or backend (newer versions), with careful coordination to avoid double migration.\n\n2. **Field-Level Migrations**: Individual migration functions handle specific schema version changes, from simple property moves (v2) to complex datasource reference transformations (v33) to field configuration updates (v42).\n\n3. **Frontend Defaults Application**: The backend explicitly applies frontend DashboardModel and PanelModel constructor defaults to ensure consistency between frontend and backend processing.\n\n4. **Datasource Index Caching**: Migrations that reference datasources use a cached indexing system for efficient O(1) lookups.\n\n5. **Conversion Status Tracking**: The conversion layer tracks conversion metadata including source/target versions and any errors that occurred.\n\n6. **Version Pinning**: Schema version 42 is explicitly marked as final, with future panel-specific migrations to be implemented in individual panel plugin migration handlers rather than as new dashboard schema versions.\n"
